channel.title: ERROR: Tor Bootstrap Result:
channel.description:
I updated Tor Browser to Tor Browser 6.0.3 based on Mozilla Firefox 45.3.0 . But After update , Error happened .
ERROR: Tor Bootstrap Result: Tor's Control Port could not be reached!
Troubleshooting: - Confirm that Whonix-Gateway is running. - Run whonixcheck on Whonix-Gateway and confirm success. - If you’re running multiple Whonix-Workstations simultaneously, confirm that separate IP addresses are configured (see https://www.whonix.org/wiki/Multiple_Whonix-Workstations). - Rerun whonixcheck here in this Whonix-Workstation.
(Technical information:) (Code: 255) (tor_bootstrap_timeout_type: none) (tor_bootstrap_status: Socket error: Received empty socket content.) (check_socks_port_open_test: 22) (Tor Circuit: not established)
I don't know how to solve this problem . I tried to run whonixcheck on Whonix-Gateway and confirm success. I tried to run whonixcheck on Whonix-Workstation , also .
But , Problem can't solve ... Please tell me the solution answer .

item.title: ERROR: Tor Bootstrap Result:
item.dc:creator: Patrick
item.description:
No more debug output required!

Bug fixed in git:

github.com/Whonix/anon-gw-anonymizer-config

update /usr/share/tor/tor-service-defaults-torrc 

For compatibility with Tor version 0.2.8.6-1~d80.jessie+1.
/var/run/tor/control was no longer created and Tor throwing a warning.
Aug 03 21:56:34.000 [warn] Permissions on directory...
by adrelanos on 10:22PM - 03 Aug 16
changed 1 files with 8 additions and 3 deletions.

Updated anon-gw-anonymizer-config package testers package coming soon.

Read full topic

item.title: ERROR: Tor Bootstrap Result:
item.dc:creator: Patrick
item.description:
Still using Whonix 12 is the problem. It most likely upgraded Tor from deb.torproject.org automatically. (Which we no longer do in Whonix 13.)

Upgrading to Whonix 13 however would not fix this issue. [It would disable deb.torproject.org but not downgrade the Tor package.]

I’ve reported a bug against Tor.
/var/run/tor/control socket not created because of /var/run/tor permission issue
https://trac.torproject.org/projects/tor/ticket/19824

Read full topic

item.title: ERROR: Tor Bootstrap Result:
item.dc:creator: Temple
item.description:
Just to add I’ve booted up Whonix on my laptop still using version 12, and this error has just started happening for me tonight, Gateway connects fine and whonixcheck runs fine, soon as I load up the workstation I get the error the others are reporting here on the Workstation.

One gateway, one workstation on my laptop, no settings changed since last use 2-3 days ago.

Edit/////

I know what the cause is, gateway will update tor geoipv6 once the update has ran the workstation will not run whonixcheck and gives the above error.

I’ve got Whonix on 4 machines, i’ve manage to replicate the error now on all 4 with the above information

Read full topic

item.title: ERROR: Tor Bootstrap Result:
item.dc:creator: torjunkie
item.description:
Hi,

I have the same problem. But I think it relates to a regression in curl updates that were just pushed (?).

Basically:

a) whonixcheck on the whonix-gw (sys-whonix) shows everything is fine;
b) whonixcheck on the whonix-ws (anon-whonix) shows the error that the first commentator is noting
c) whonixcheck -v output in the workstation shows:

[INFO] [whonixcheck] anon-whonix | Whonix-Workstation | whonix-ws Template-Based AppVM | Wed Aug 3 17:08:25 UTC 2016
[INFO] [whonixcheck] Input Detection: INPUT_AUTO=true CLI=true GUI=false
stdin connected to terminal. Using cli output. Not using gui output.
Alternatively, if want to run from command line, but still use the graphical user interface for input, you could add to command line: --gui
[INFO] [whonixcheck] Root Check Result: Ok, not running as root.
[INFO] [whonixcheck] Pin torproject.org certificate: disabled.
[INFO] [whonixcheck] Qubes Settings Test Result: Ok. (GATEWAY_IP: 10.137.3.1)
[INFO] [whonixcheck] Qubes Settings Test Result: Ok, qubes_vm_type is AppVM.
[INFO] [whonixcheck] Check Kernel Messages Test Result: Found nothing remarkable, ok.
[INFO] [whonixcheck] Check whonixsetup Result: done, ok.
[INFO] [whonixcheck] Check Package Manager Running Result: None running, ok.
[INFO] [whonixcheck] check network interfaces Result: Ok.
[INFO] [whonixcheck] Tor Check Result: Not running on Whonix-Gateway, ok.
[INFO] [whonixcheck] Tor Config Check Result: Not running on Whonix-Gateway, ok.
[INFO] [whonixcheck] Tor Pid Check Result: Not running on Whonix-Gateway., ok.
[INFO] [whonixcheck] Tor SocksPort Reachability Test Result: Reachable. (curl exit code: 22 | curl status message: [22] - [HTTP page not retrieved. The requested url was not found or returned another error with the HTTP error code being 400 or above. This return code only appears if -f, --fail is used.])
[ERROR] [whonixcheck] Tor Bootstrap Result:
Tor’s Control Port could not be reached!

Troubleshooting:

  • Confirm that Whonix-Gateway is running.

  • Run whonixcheck on Whonix-Gateway and confirm success.

  • Rerun whonixcheck here in this Whonix-Workstation.

(Technical information:)
(Code: 255)
(tor_bootstrap_timeout_type: none)
(tor_bootstrap_status: Socket error: Received empty socket content.)
(check_socks_port_open_test: 22)
(Tor Circuit: not established)

Everything was fine just before those updates were installed. I was on testers repository though. Changing the repository to stable and re-running apt-get update && apt-get dist-upgrade doesn’t solve the problem.

Neither does creating a new workstation appVM.

Ironically, Tor Browser works just fine - both 6.0.3 & the new hardened 6.5a2.

I’m sure Patrick will have an answer

Read full topic
